# hilavitkutin — backlog

## Windows os-tier

Current os-tier covers Linux + macOS via mmap + pthread +
clock_gettime. Windows needs VirtualAlloc + CreateThread +
QueryPerformanceCounter wrappers. Defer until a Windows consumer
surfaces or the distribution story demands it.

## no_os tier documentation

The no_os tier is trait-only — consumers ship their own
MemoryProviderApi / ThreadPoolApi / ClockApi impls. A concrete
example (for an embedded target) would help third-party
adoption. Defer until a consumer surfaces.

## Memory protection (mprotect)

`OsMemoryProvider::protect` stubs to Ok this round. Real mprotect
integration with the read/write flag combinations lands with the
persistence follow-up round that actually exercises protection
(memory-mapped file rehydration).

## ThreadPool tests

Pool primitives ship without dedicated tests this round; dispatch
round (5a3) exercises them against the fused-WU monomorphised
function. Adding targeted unit tests here would add negative
value today.

