## Engine 5a3 follow-ups

The 5a3 round ships the dispatch (domain 17) + intrinsics
(domain 13) type surface with stub code-gen bodies. Each entry
below is a separate downstream round.

- `select_approach` body — record-count thresholds (10K cutover
  between IndirectPerFiber/TrunkMega and ScheduleMega; exact
  boundary is benchmarked).
- `codegen_fiber` body — emit the monomorphised per-fiber
  dispatch function. Needs LLVM hooks or a build-time plugin
  from hilavitkutin-build (ExpandedLto pragma).
- `codegen_core` body — emit the per-core pipeline: encodes
  phases + morsel boundaries + sync points + per-fiber dispatch
  records. Depends on `codegen_fiber`.
- ExpandedLto pragma integration — required for the LLVM
  devirtualisation of the `&[WuFn]` slice into straight-line
  code. Depends on hilavitkutin-build 5a4+.
- Rust-pipe pattern wiring — stack-cached resource snapshot at
  morsel head, fiber-input column reads at morsel start,
  DSE-friendly internal column reads, grouped output stores at
  morsel tail. Depends on `codegen_fiber` body.
- Progress counter thread-safety stress tests — loom / miri
  coverage over the Release-store / Acquire-load contract.
- Intrinsics: real `core::intrinsics::prefetch_*` wiring on
  nightly (gated behind a `nightly-intrinsics` feature; the
  current `intrinsics-std` feature only enables `core::hint`
  + `core::sync::atomic::compiler_fence`).
- Intrinsics: platform-specific inline asm paths (x86_64
  PREFETCHT0, aarch64 PRFM). Useful when the LLVM intrinsic
  doesn't emit the exact instruction the profile wants.

## Engine 5a4 follow-ups

The 5a4 round ships the thread (domain 20) + adapt (domain 22)
type surface with stub coordination/decision bodies. Each entry
below is a separate downstream round.

### Threading follow-ups

- Actual pthread / Win32 / OS-thread spawning (gated on a future
  `threading-std` feature; introduces the feature flag + spawn
  method on `ThreadPool` together).
- Hybrid spin-park wake implementation — 128 spin iters default
  via `core::hint::spin_loop`, then park on a platform primitive
  (futex on Linux, `ulock_wait` on macOS, `WaitOnAddress` on
  Windows).
- Heterogeneous-core detection — CPUID leaf 0x1A on x86, sysfs
  (`/sys/devices/cpu_core` vs `/sys/devices/cpu_atom`) on Linux,
  IOKit / hwloc on macOS.
- Core pinning per platform — `pthread_setaffinity_np` on Linux,
  `thread_policy_set` with `THREAD_AFFINITY_POLICY` on macOS,
  `SetThreadAffinityMask` on Windows.
- Work-stealing `Executor` trait — consumer-provided override for
  variable per-record workloads. `steal_fallback` stub gains a
  real `Executor` bound once the trait ships.
- Head+tail convergence merge implementations — addition path
  for additive/commutative accumulators; sequential fallback for
  non-commutative fibers. Both need `Convergence::meeting_record`
  semantics (whichever thread crosses midpoint first publishes).
- Phase pipeline parallelism wiring — `ProgressCounter` exists
  from 5a3; the thread scheduler has to consult it between
  phases so phase N+1 starts as soon as N produces a morsel's
  worth.
- `classify_cores` signature should become `<const MAX_CORES: usize>`
  generic instead of hard-coded `[CoreClass; 256]` once a
  follow-up round needs the flexibility.

### Adapt follow-ups

- PMC / `perf_event` integration for `cache_miss_rate` and
  `branch_miss_rate` sampling (Linux `perf_event_open`, macOS
  `kpc`, Windows PerfCounter APIs).
- Phase completion time measurement — monotonic clock via the
  `hilavitkutin-api::Clock` trait (already shipped in platform
  round); wire into `AdaptMetrics::phase_completion_time_ns`.
- Adaptive mode selection heuristic — latency vs throughput
  trade-off feeding `select_adapt_config`. EMA-based per DESIGN
  (1/8 decay).
- Per-phase config hot-swap during pipeline execution — between
  frames only, per DESIGN (during-execution swaps would
  invalidate monomorphised dispatch).
- Telemetry hooks for exporting adapt decisions to the consumer
  (observability / tuning dashboards, hung on a future trait).
